search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?asname ?cuname ?coname ?cname WHERE { ?as wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2596 ?cu ; wdt:P17 ?co . ?co wdt:P30 ?c . ?c wdt:P31 wd:Q5107 . ?as <http://schema.org/name> ?asname . ?cu <http://schema.org/name> ?cuname . ?co <http://schema.org/name> ?coname . ?c <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } LIMIT 30

search_workflow.narrative: Now I count the archeaological site for each country and find the country that has more
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?c ?cname (count(?as) as ?num_arc_site) WHERE { ?as wdt:P17 ?c . ?as wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?as <http://schema.org/name> ?asname . ?c <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } ORDER BY DESC (?num_arc_site) LIMIT 1

search_workflow.narrative: Now i look for the IRI of human settlements
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?o ?oname WHERE { ?as wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P31 ?o . ?as <http://schema.org/name> ?name . ?o <http://schema.org/name> ?oname . FILTER REGEX(?oname, "human sett") } LIMIT 50

search_workflow.narrative: Now I get Q486972 --> human settlement and find the country that has more human settlement
search_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?c ?cname (count( DISTINCT ?hs) as ?num_human_settlement) WHERE { ?hs wdt:P17 ?c . ?hs wdt:P31 wd:Q486972 . ?hs <http://schema.org/name> ?hsname . ?c <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } ORDER BY DESC (?num_human_settlement) LIMIT 1
